^C:CREDITS
:-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Credits for individual WADs are provided on each page but where a mod is used broadly across many pages (such as enhancements, fixes and gameplay modifications), as best as is possible, a list of credits and sources is provided here. This information has been taken from whatever public sources are available; apologies for any mistakes.

(In alphabetical order:)


:Chocolate Doom / Heretic / Hexen / Strife - <chocolate-doom.org>
:===============================================================================
`Chocolate Doom` is written by _Simon Howard_, with extensive help from many other people who have provided patches, bug reports and suggestions.

`Chocolate Strife` was developed by _James Haley_ and _Samuel Villarreal_ as part of a painstaking reverse engineering project.

:Crispy Doom - <github.com/fabiangreffrath/crispy-doom>
:===============================================================================
*"Crispy Doom is a friendly fork of Chocolate Doom that provides a higher display resolution, removes the static limits of the Doom engine and offers further optional visual, tactical and physical enhancements while remaining entirely config file, savegame, netplay and demo compatible with the original."

By _Fabian Greffrath_.

